    <item>
      <title>Alerts</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/docs/shortcodes/alerts/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 22 Nov 2022 13:42:31 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/docs/shortcodes/alerts/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;adding-a-page-alert&#34;&gt;Adding a Page Alert &lt;a href=&#34;#adding-a-page-alert&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Page alerts can be added to your markdown using the following shortcode:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;prism-codeblock &#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;pre id=&#34;0cec4be&#34; class=&#34;language-go &#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;code&gt;{{&amp;lt; alert text=&amp;#34;This is the default alert. It consists of a default theme colour and icon.&amp;#34; /&amp;gt;}}&lt;/code&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/pre&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The above code results in the following alert:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-default d-flex&#34; role=&#34;alert&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;flex-shrink-1 alert-icon&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &lt;span class=&#34;material-icons size-20 me-2&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  notifications&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34;&gt;This is the default alert. It consists of a default theme colour and icon.&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;alert-with-context&#34;&gt;Alert with Context &lt;a href=&#34;#alert-with-context&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Add context to an alert via the &lt;code&gt;context&lt;/code&gt; parameter:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Tables</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/docs/shortcodes/tables/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 05 Nov 2022 04:41:15 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/docs/shortcodes/tables/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;table&lt;/code&gt; shortcode enables Lotus Docs to take advantage of &lt;a href=&#34;https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.2/content/tables&#34; rel=&#34;external&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Bootstrap&amp;rsquo;s opt-in table styling&lt;svg width=&#34;16&#34; height=&#34;16&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; d=&#34;M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;regular-tables&#34;&gt;Regular Tables &lt;a href=&#34;#regular-tables&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;By default Lotus Docs renders regular Markdown tables with some very basic styling:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Tabs</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/docs/shortcodes/tabs/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 25 Apr 2023 03:51:15 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/docs/shortcodes/tabs/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;tabs&lt;/code&gt; shortcode leverages &lt;a href=&#34;https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.3/components/navs-tabs/#tabs&#34; rel=&#34;external&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Bootstrap&amp;rsquo;s Tabs styling&lt;svg width=&#34;16&#34; height=&#34;16&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; d=&#34;M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to easily add Tabs to your markdown content. The shortcode is actually a combination of two separate shortcodes (&lt;code&gt;tab&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;tabs&lt;/code&gt;) working together.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Prism</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/docs/shortcodes/prism/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 28 Nov 2022 04:05:31 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/docs/shortcodes/prism/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;prism-shortcode&#34;&gt;Prism Shortcode &lt;a href=&#34;#prism-shortcode&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;When Prism is enabled in &lt;code&gt;hugo.toml&lt;/code&gt; syntax highlighting can also be achieved using a paired Prism shortcode. The code language is declared using the &lt;code&gt;lang&lt;/code&gt; parameter:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;prism-codeblock &#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;pre id=&#34;793d8e3&#34; class=&#34;language-go &#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;code&gt;{{&amp;lt; prism lang=&amp;#34;html&amp;#34; &amp;gt;}}&#xA;&amp;lt;html&amp;gt;&#xA;  &amp;lt;head&amp;gt;&#xA;    &amp;lt;title&amp;gt;Buy cool new product&amp;lt;/title&amp;gt;&#xA;  &amp;lt;/head&amp;gt;&#xA;  &amp;lt;body&amp;gt;&#xA;    &amp;lt;!-- Use action=&amp;#34;/create-checkout-session.php&amp;#34; if your server is PHP based. --&amp;gt;&#xA;    &amp;lt;form action=&amp;#34;/create-checkout-session&amp;#34; method=&amp;#34;POST&amp;#34;&amp;gt;&#xA;      &amp;lt;button type=&amp;#34;submit&amp;#34;&amp;gt;Checkout&amp;lt;/button&amp;gt;&#xA;    &amp;lt;/form&amp;gt;&#xA;  &amp;lt;/body&amp;gt;&#xA;&amp;lt;/html&amp;gt;&#xA;{{&amp;lt; /prism &amp;gt;}}&lt;/code&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/pre&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;All code blocks highlighted by Prism feature the &lt;a href=&#34;https://prismjs.com/plugins/copy-to-clipboard/&#34; rel=&#34;external&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Copy to Clipboard Button&lt;svg width=&#34;16&#34; height=&#34;16&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; d=&#34;M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; plugin. Hover over (or tap if on mobile) the examples above and the copy button appears in the top right hand corner of the code block. Click this button to copy the code to your clipboard.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Markdownify</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/docs/shortcodes/markdownify/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 28 Apr 2023 16:35:15 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/docs/shortcodes/markdownify/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This shortcode parses its content as markdown.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;usage&#34;&gt;Usage &lt;a href=&#34;#usage&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The following:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;prism-codeblock &#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;pre id=&#34;65380b9&#34; class=&#34;language-go &#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;code&gt;{{&amp;lt; markdownify &amp;gt;}}&#xA;&#xA;**Bold Text**: Above a code block.&#xA;&#xA;```html&#xA;&amp;lt;!-- An example HTML code block --&amp;gt;&#xA;&amp;lt;h1&amp;gt;Hello World&amp;lt;/h1&amp;gt;&#xA;&#xA;{{&amp;lt; /markdownify &amp;gt;}}&lt;/code&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/pre&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Renders:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bold Text&lt;/strong&gt;: Above a code block.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;prism-codeblock &#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;pre id=&#34;d253643&#34; class=&#34;language-html &#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;!-- An example HTML code block --&amp;gt;&#xA;&amp;lt;h1&amp;gt;Hello World&amp;lt;/h1&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/pre&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;nested-shortcodes&#34;&gt;Nested Shortcodes &lt;a href=&#34;#nested-shortcodes&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;markdownify&lt;/code&gt; shortcode is especially useful in cases where you require portions of content nested inside another shortcode be parsed as Markdown.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>KaTex</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/docs/shortcodes/katex/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 27 Aug 2023 04:13:11 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/docs/shortcodes/katex/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Lotus Docs has &lt;a data-bs-delay=&#34;{&amp;#34;hide&amp;#34;:300,&amp;#34;show&amp;#34;:550}&#34; data-bs-html=&#34;true&#34; data-bs-title=&#34;&lt;a href=&#39;//localhost:1313/docs/features/katex/&#39;&gt;&lt;p&gt;FEATURES&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KaTex&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Fast Tex math rendering for your Lotus Docs site&lt;/a&gt;&#34; data-bs-toggle=&#34;tooltip&#34; href=&#34;//localhost:1313/docs/features/katex/&#34;&gt;built-in support&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=&#34;https://katex.org/&#34; rel=&#34;external&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;KaTex&lt;svg width=&#34;16&#34; height=&#34;16&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; d=&#34;M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. However, there are certain equation syntaxes which do not render well if at all without a lot of character escaping&lt;sup id=&#34;fnref:1&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:1&#34; class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; role=&#34;doc-noteref&#34;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; or alterations. The KaTex shortcode is suited to handle such cases.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
